Observed Data (Monthly and Annual) - These values are the
means and extremes for the Period of Record (number of
years) indicated. Period of record are documented in the
Local Climatological Data annual publications.
GENERAL TABLE NOTES:

All tables start with city name, years of record, followed by the

monthly and annual values of the parameter.


T INDICATES TRACE PRECIPITATION, AN AMOUNT GREATER THAN ZERO BUT LESS THAN THE LOWEST REPORTABLE VALUE.
 

BLANK ENTRIES DENOTE MISSING OR UNREPORTED DATA.


NORMALS ARE 30-YEAR AVERAGES (1971 - 2000).


WIND DIRECTION IS RECORDED IN TENS OF DEGREES (2 DIGITS) CLOCKWISE FROM TRUE NORTH. ďż˝00ďż˝ INDICATES CALM. ďż˝36ďż˝ INDICATES TRUE NORTH.
